Notes by Mark Petersen:

I split the file cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40 into four, for the 
first through fourth pronounciation:

grep -v '(' cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40 > cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40_1
grep '(2)' --color=never cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40 > cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40_2
grep '(3)' --color=never cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40 > cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40_3
grep '(4)' --color=never cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40 > cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40_4

I then removed the character-only lines from cmudict.0.7a_SPHINX_40_1.
Then remove the (2) etc in vim with %s/(2)//g.
